activecallTable.name: activecallTable
activecallTable.description: A table of active call information.

activecallEntry.name: activecallEntry
activecallEntry.description: A row in the active call table.

actcallUsername.name: actcallUsername
actcallUsername.description: Name of the user associated with this call. A null string is returned if the call is active but the current user name cannot be determined at the time of the call.

actcallCallingNumber.name: actcallCallingNumber
actcallCallingNumber.description: The number from which this call was made. Can be a null string. This object obsoletes the callSetupCallingNbr object.

actcallCalledNumber.name: actcallCalledNumber
actcallCalledNumber.description: The number to which this call was made. Can be a null string. This object obsoletes the callSetupCalledNbr object.

actcallSPBName.name: actcallSPBName
actcallSPBName.description: Session Parameter Block name. The RAC determines how to handle a call through the SPB. The SPB is defined in the configuration file. When a call comes in, the RAC tries to match the received setup information elements that accompanied the call with the values in the setup criteria section of the defined SPBs. The first SPB that matches the call's setup criteria is used.

actcallDeviceType.name: actcallDeviceType
actcallDeviceType.description: An enumerated integer indicating the port type. asy(1) - the call is assigned internally to an asynchronous device (async port). syn(9) - the call is handled internally by a synchronous device (sync port). ta(10) - the call is handled internally by a ta device (ta port). mp(12) - pseudo-session, Multi-link PPP bundle head. This object obsoletes the callSetupPortType object.

actcallDeviceNumber.name: actcallDeviceNumber
actcallDeviceNumber.description: The one-based device (port) number the call is assigned to. This object in conjunction with the object, actcallDeviceType, should be used to cross-reference the information displayed by the CLI command 'who'. This object obsoletes the callSetupPortNumber object.

actcallSubAddress.name: actcallSubAddress
actcallSubAddress.description: The subaddress this call is connected to. Can be a null string. This object obsoletes the callSetupCalledSubAddr object.

actcallBearer.name: actcallBearer
actcallBearer.description: This object defines the bearer capability of the incoming call. This object obsoletes the callSetupBearer object.

actcallSetupTime.name: actcallSetupTime
actcallSetupTime.description: The time that the call started. This is RAC system time, which is the same as Unix system time: seconds since 0:00 January 1, 1970 UTC (GMT). This object obsoletes callSetupCallingTime.

actcallDuration.name: actcallDuration
actcallDuration.description: Duration of the phone call, in seconds.

actcalllocalin.name: actcalllocalin
actcalllocalin.description: The Internet (IP) address assigned to the RAC end of a point-to-point link established during this call, in dotted-decimal notation.

actcallremotein.name: actcallremotein
actcallremotein.description: The Internet (IP) address assigned to the far end of a point-to-point link established during this call, in dotted-decimal notation.

actcalllocalat.name: actcalllocalat
actcalllocalat.description: The local AppleTalk address assigned to this call.

actcallremoteat.name: actcallremoteat
actcallremoteat.description: The remote AppleTalk address assigned to this call.

actcalllocalipx.name: actcalllocalipx
actcalllocalipx.description: The local IPX address assigned to this call.

actcallremoteipx.name: actcallremoteipx
actcallremoteipx.description: The remote IPX address assigned to this call.

actcallConnectionType.name: actcallConnectionType
actcallConnectionType.description: The name of the client routine running on the port at the time of this call.

actcallOctetsRx.name: actcallOctetsRx
actcallOctetsRx.description: The number of octets received during this call.

actcallOctetsTx.name: actcallOctetsTx
actcallOctetsTx.description: The number of octets transmitted during this call.

actcallOrigin.name: actcallOrigin
actcallOrigin.description: The call origin. incoming(1) - the RAC answered an incoming call. outgoing(2) - the RAC made the call. This object obsoletes the callSetupCallType object.

actcallCallState.name: actcallCallState
actcallCallState.description: The current state of this call. invalid(1)-call is inactive and the contents of this table row are not valid. valid(2)- call is active and contents of this table row are valid.

actcallConfiguredType.name: actcallConfiguredType
actcallConfiguredType.description: The type (mode) of the port at the time of the connection. cli - allows an incoming session access to the CLI. The CLI provides access to the network and connections to other hosts via the telnet, connect, rlogin and tn3270 commands. slip - allows a port to perform as a network interface using SLIP. IP packets are encapsulated by SLIP. ppp - allows a port to perform as a network interface using PPP. Packets of several protocols are encapsulated by PPP. arap - allows a port to perform as a network interface using ARAP. slave - allows a port to accept TCP connections over the network. connect - allows a port to communicate with a LAT host via the connect command. rlogin - allows a port to communicate via the rlogin command. telnet - allows a port to communicate via the telnet command. tn3270 - allows a port to communicate via the tn3270 command.

actcallOwningBundle.name: actcallOwningBundle
actcallOwningBundle.description: The identifier of the MP bundle that owns this PPP link.

actCallTable.description: A table of active call information.

actCallEntry.name: actCallEntry
actCallEntry.description: A row in the active call table.

This object obsoletes the callSetupPortType object.

activeCallCalledNumber.name: activeCallCalledNumber
activeCallCalledNumber.description: The number to which this call was made. Can be a null string. This object obsoletes the callSetupCalledNbr object.

activeCallDuration.description: Duration of the phone call, in seconds.

activeCalllocalin.description: The Internet (IP) address assigned to the RAC end of a point-to-point link established during this call, in dotted-decimal notation.

activeCallremoteipx.name: activeCallremoteipx

activeCallConnectionType.description: The name of the client routine running on the port at the time of this call.

activeCallOctetsTx.name: activeCallOctetsTx

activeCallOrigin.name: activeCallOrigin
activeCallOrigin.description: The call origin. incoming(1) - the RAC answered an incoming call. outgoing(2) - the RAC made the call. This object obsoletes the callSetupCallType object.

activeCallCallState.name: activeCallCallState
activeCallCallState.description: The current state of this call. invalid(1)-call is inactive and the contents of this table row are not valid. valid(2)- call is active and contents of this table row are valid.

activeCallConfiguredType.name: activeCallConfiguredType
activeCallConfiguredType.description: The type (mode) of the port at the time of the connection. cli - allows an incoming session access to the CLI. The CLI provides access to the network and connections to other hosts via the telnet, connect, rlogin and tn3270 commands. slip - allows a port to perform as a network interface using SLIP. IP packets are encapsulated by SLIP. ppp - allows a port to perform as a network interface using PPP. Packets of several protocols are encapsulated by PPP. arap - allows a port to perform as a network interface using ARAP. slave - allows a port to accept TCP connections over the network. connect - allows a port to communicate with a LAT host via the connect command. rlogin - allows a port to communicate via the rlogin command. telnet - allows a port to communicate via the telnet command. tn3270 - allows a port to communicate via the tn3270 command.

activeCallOwningBundle.name: activeCallOwningBundle
activeCallOwningBundle.description: The identifier of the MP bundle that owns this PPP link. This number will always be the same as the mp device number. For example, mp17 devtype will have a owningBundle number of 17

activeCallLocalAt.name: activeCallLocalAt
activeCallLocalAt.description: The local AppleTalk address assigned to this call.

activeCallRemoteAt.name: activeCallRemoteAt
activeCallRemoteAt.description: The remote AppleTalk address assigned to this call.

actCallAsyTable.name: actCallAsyTable
actCallAsyTable.description: A table of modem call statistics indexed by the async device number (which is identical to the modem number)

actCallAsyEntry.name: actCallAsyEntry
actCallAsyEntry.description: A row in the modem call statistics table.

activeCallAsyBeginRxSpeed.name: activeCallAsyBeginRxSpeed
activeCallAsyBeginRxSpeed.description: The receive connect speed at the time the call was established. Note: The agent will return zero if the modem is not in a busy state.

activeCallAsyCurrRxSpeed.name: activeCallAsyCurrRxSpeed
activeCallAsyCurrRxSpeed.description: The current receive connect speed of the call.

activeCallAsyBeginTxSpeed.name: activeCallAsyBeginTxSpeed
activeCallAsyBeginTxSpeed.description: The transmit connect speed at the time the call was established. Note: The agent will return zero if the modem is not in a busy state.

activeCallAsyCurrTxSpeed.name: activeCallAsyCurrTxSpeed
activeCallAsyCurrTxSpeed.description: The current transmit connect speed of the call.

activeCallAsyTxBaudRate.name: activeCallAsyTxBaudRate
activeCallAsyTxBaudRate.description: The rate at which symbols that carry data are generated. Symbol rate limits and options apply to the modem v.34. Default is r2400(1).

activeCallAsyRxBaudRate.name: activeCallAsyRxBaudRate
activeCallAsyRxBaudRate.description: The rate at which symbols that carry data are received. Symbol rate limits and options apply to the modem v.34. Default is r2400(1).

activeCallAsyCurrSignalQ.name: activeCallAsyCurrSignalQ
activeCallAsyCurrSignalQ.description: Current line signal quality. This is a unitless number derived from several line characteristics. Range is 0-255; 0 is good. 30 or less is reasonable.

activeCallAsyBeginRxLineLevel.name: activeCallAsyBeginRxLineLevel
activeCallAsyBeginRxLineLevel.description: The receive signal level at the beginning of the call, in dBm (ratio of receive level to a reference value). The number returned by this MIB object is positive, but it represents a negative number (ie, this object returns the negative of the actual dBm). Expected values are roughly -12 to -30. Less than -11 is bad; that signal is too strong, and causes problems for the modem.

activeCallAsyCurrRxLineLevel.name: activeCallAsyCurrRxLineLevel
activeCallAsyCurrRxLineLevel.description: The current receive signal level of the call, in dBm (ratio of receive level to a reference value). The number returned by this MIB object is positive, but it represents a negative number (ie, this object returns the negative of the actual dBm). Expected values are roughly -12 to -30. Less than -11 is bad; that signal is too strong, and causes problems for the modem.

activeCallAsyErrorProtocol.name: activeCallAsyErrorProtocol
activeCallAsyErrorProtocol.description: Error correction protocol used by the modem.

activeCallAsyCompressionProtocol.name: activeCallAsyCompressionProtocol
activeCallAsyCompressionProtocol.description: Data compression protocol used by the modem. The compression protocol used by the modem is dependent on the error correction protocol used at the lower layer.

activeCallAsyTxPackets.name: activeCallAsyTxPackets
activeCallAsyTxPackets.description: The number of LAPM packets sent by the modem. This does not include retransmitted packets.

activeCallAsyTxPacketError.name: activeCallAsyTxPacketError
activeCallAsyTxPacketError.description: The number of LAPM packets retransmitted by the modem.

activeCallAsyRxPackets.name: activeCallAsyRxPackets
activeCallAsyRxPackets.description: The number of good LAPM packets received by the modem.

activeCallAsyRxPacketError.name: activeCallAsyRxPacketError
activeCallAsyRxPacketError.description: The number of bad LAPM packets (with CRC errors) received by the modem.

activeCallAsyRetrainReqSent.name: activeCallAsyRetrainReqSent
activeCallAsyRetrainReqSent.description: The number of retrains requested by the modem for this call.

activeCallAsyRetrainReqReceived.name: activeCallAsyRetrainReqReceived
activeCallAsyRetrainReqReceived.description: The number of retrain requests received by the modem from the remote modem for this call.

activeCallAsyRRNReqReceived.name: activeCallAsyRRNReqReceived
activeCallAsyRRNReqReceived.description: Number of rate renegotiation request (RRN) initiated by the remote modem.

activeCallAsyRRNReqSent.name: activeCallAsyRRNReqSent
activeCallAsyRRNReqSent.description: Number of rate renegotiation request (RRN) initiated by this modem.

activeCallAsyRoundTripDelay.name: activeCallAsyRoundTripDelay
activeCallAsyRoundTripDelay.description: The round trip delay, in milliseconds, for this call. This object alongwith the object, activeCallAsyFarEndEchoFreq, gives the echo characteristics of the call.

activeCallAsyFarEndEchoFreq.name: activeCallAsyFarEndEchoFreq
activeCallAsyFarEndEchoFreq.description: Far end echo frequency offset, in Hertz. This object alongwith the object, activeCallAsyRoundTripDelay, gives the echo characteristics of the call.

activeCallAsyFarEndEchoLevel.name: activeCallAsyFarEndEchoLevel
activeCallAsyFarEndEchoLevel.description: Far end echo level, in decibels. The number represents the negative decibels.

activeCallAsyOscFreqOffset.name: activeCallAsyOscFreqOffset
activeCallAsyOscFreqOffset.description: Oscillator frequency offset, in PPM. Not always valid.

activeCallAsySNR.name: activeCallAsySNR
activeCallAsySNR.description: Signal to noise ratio in decibels. Low is bad, high is good. Zero means not valid: no current connection, or connection is not V.34 (other protocols don't calculate this).

activeCallAsyx2Status.name: activeCallAsyx2Status
activeCallAsyx2Status.description: x2 phase bit map --------------------- | 4 | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 | bits --------------------- |DM |P4 |P3 |P2 |P1 | --------------------- P1 = 1 Detected In Phase 1 P2 = 1 Detected In Phase 2 P3 = 1 X2 In Phase 3 P4 = 1 X2 In Phase 4 DM = 1 X2 In Data Mode

activeCallAsyx2RbsStatus.name: activeCallAsyx2RbsStatus
activeCallAsyx2RbsStatus.description: x2 raw bit signalling, bit map ------------------------- | 5 | 4 | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 | bits ------------------------- |S5 |S4 |S3 |S2 |S1 |S0 | ------------------------- S0 = 1 RBS in symbol 0 S1 = 1 RBS in symbol 1 S2 = 1 RBS in symbol 2 S3 = 1 RBS in symbol 3 S4 = 1 RBS in symbol 4 S5 = 1 RBS in symbol 5

activeCallAsyk56Status.name: activeCallAsyk56Status
activeCallAsyk56Status.description: k56 phase bit map --------------------- | 4 | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 | bits --------------------- |DM |P4 |P3 |P2 |P1 | --------------------- P1 = 1 Detected In Phase 1 P2 = 1 Detected In Phase 2 P3 = 1 K56 In Phase 3 P4 = 1 K56 In Phase 4 DM = 1 K56 In Data Mode

activeCallAsyk56RbsStatus.name: activeCallAsyk56RbsStatus
activeCallAsyk56RbsStatus.description: k56 raw bit signalling, bit map ------------------------- | 5 | 4 | 3 | 2 | 1 | 0 | bits ------------------------- |S5 |S4 |S3 |S2 |S1 |S0 | ------------------------- S0 = 1 RBS in symbol 0 S1 = 1 RBS in symbol 1 S2 = 1 RBS in symbol 2 S3 = 1 RBS in symbol 3 S4 = 1 RBS in symbol 4 S5 = 1 RBS in symbol 5

activeCallAsyWANUnitNumber.name: activeCallAsyWANUnitNumber
activeCallAsyWANUnitNumber.description: The physical WAN module unit number in the RAC that uses WAN modules. The range is 1 to anxt1Total. Use anxt1WanModuleTable to retrieve the unit's ifIndex number.(For R14.1 and later releases, WAN1=1001 and WAN2 = 1002 always

activeCallAsyChannel.name: activeCallAsyChannel
activeCallAsyChannel.description: A number from 1 to anxt1TotChan that identifies which DS0 channel handled the call.

activeCallAsyx2SpeedReduction.name: activeCallAsyx2SpeedReduction
activeCallAsyx2SpeedReduction.description: Speed reduction due to spectral shaping: 0 no speed reduction 1 speed reduction of 1.333 kBps 2 speed reduction of 2.666 kBps 3 speed reduction of 4.0 kBps 4 speed reduction of 5.333 kBps 5 speed reduction of 6.666 kBps 6 speed reduction of 8.0 kBps

activeCallAsyk56SpeedReduction.name: activeCallAsyk56SpeedReduction
activeCallAsyk56SpeedReduction.description: Speed reduction due to robbed bits: 0 no speed reduction 1 speed reduction of 2.0 kBps 2 speed reduction of 4.0 kBps 3 speed reduction of 6.0 kBps 4 speed reduction of 8.0 kBps

activeCallAsyV90Status.name: activeCallAsyV90Status
activeCallAsyV90Status.description: V90 status (this is a bitmap): 1 = currently in V90 mode 2 = V90 detected in phase 1 4 = V90 detected in phase 2 8 = V90 through phase 3 16 = V90 through phase 4 32 = V90 in data mode 64 = V90 data mode at least once

activeCallAsyV90LookAhead.name: activeCallAsyV90LookAhead
activeCallAsyV90LookAhead.description: Number of look ahead CSS frames.

actCallTaTable.name: actCallTaTable
actCallTaTable.description: A table of TA call statistics indexed by the TA device number.

actCallTaEntry.name: actCallTaEntry
actCallTaEntry.description: A row in the TA call statistics table.

activeCallTaSpeed.name: activeCallTaSpeed
activeCallTaSpeed.description: The receive connect speed at the time the call was established.

actCallSyncTable.name: actCallSyncTable
actCallSyncTable.description: A table of Sync call statistics indexed by the Sync device number.

actCallSyncEntry.name: actCallSyncEntry
actCallSyncEntry.description: A row in the Sync call statistics table.

activeCallSyncSpeed.name: activeCallSyncSpeed
activeCallSyncSpeed.description: The receive connect speed at the time the call was established.

actCallMpTable.name: actCallMpTable
actCallMpTable.description: A table of call history MP information/statistics.

actCallMpEntry.name: actCallMpEntry
actCallMpEntry.description: A row in the call history MP table.

activeCallMpBundleIdx.name: activeCallMpBundleIdx
activeCallMpBundleIdx.description: The identifier of this MP bundle.

callHistMaxCalls.name: callHistMaxCalls
callHistMaxCalls.description: The maximum number of calls for which history is kept by the RAC. Default is 0. Note: Assigning an arbitrarily large value to this object could affect the performance of the box due to memory being used to maintain this table. Each call record uses about 500 bytes of RAC memory.

callHistStartIdx.name: callHistStartIdx
callHistStartIdx.description: The beginning (lowest) value of callHistIndex currently in the call history table. This is the oldest call currently in the table. Note this value could change at any time since the table could have new calls added to it and old calls dropping off the table.

callHistEndIdx.name: callHistEndIdx
callHistEndIdx.description: The end (highest) value of callHistIndex in the call history table. Note this value could change at any time since the table will have new calls added whenever a call terminates.

callHistTable.name: callHistTable
callHistTable.description: A table of call history information. You should view this table as either a circular buffer or a sliding window whose size is specified by callHistMaxCalls. When the table is full and a call terminates, the information for the oldest call in the table is discarded and the new call information is added. The callHistStartIdx value is changed whenever a call's information is discarded. The callHistEndIdx value is changed whenever a call's information is added to the table.

callHistEntry.name: callHistEntry
callHistEntry.description: A row in the call history table.

callHistIndex.name: callHistIndex
callHistIndex.description: A unique identifier assigned to a call in the call history table. When a call terminates, its call record is moved from the active call table to the call history table, and the next higher history index number is assigned to it.

callHistUsername.name: callHistUsername
callHistUsername.description: Name of the user associated with this call. Can be a null string. This object obsoletes anxmStatsUsername.

callHistCallingNumber.name: callHistCallingNumber
callHistCallingNumber.description: The number from which this call was made. Can be a null string.

callHistCalledNumber.name: callHistCalledNumber
callHistCalledNumber.description: The number to which this call was made. Can be a null string. This object obsoletes anxmStatsNumber.

callHistSPBName.name: callHistSPBName
callHistSPBName.description: Session Parameter Block name used when answering the call. Can be a null string.

callHistWANUnitNumber.name: callHistWANUnitNumber
callHistWANUnitNumber.description: The physical WAN module unit number in the RAC that uses WAN modules. The range is 1 to anxt1Total. Use anxt1WanModuleTable to retrieve the unit's ifIndex number.

callHistChannel.name: callHistChannel
callHistChannel.description: A number from 1 to anxt1TotChan that identifies which DS0 channel handled the call.

callHistDeviceType.name: callHistDeviceType
callHistDeviceType.description: An enumerated integer indicating the port type. asy(1) - the call was assigned internally to an asynchronous device (async port). syn(9) - the call was handled internally by a synchronous device (sync port). ta(10) - the call was handled internally by a ta device (ta port). mp(12) - pseudo-session, Multi-link PPP bundle head.

callHistDeviceNumber.name: callHistDeviceNumber
callHistDeviceNumber.description: The 1-based device (port) number the call was assigned to. This object in conjunction with the object, callHistDeviceType, should be used to cross-reference the information displayed by the CLI command 'who'. This object obsoletes anxmStatsPort.

callHistSubAddress.name: callHistSubAddress
callHistSubAddress.description: The subaddress this call was connected to. Can be a null string.

callHistBearer.name: callHistBearer
callHistBearer.description: This object defines the bearer capability of the incoming call.

callHistSetupTime.name: callHistSetupTime
callHistSetupTime.description: The time that the call started. This is RAC system time, which is the same as Unix system time: seconds since 0:00 January 1, 1970 UTC (GMT). This object obsoletes anxmStatsTime.

callHistDuration.name: callHistDuration
callHistDuration.description: Duration of the call, in seconds. This object obsoletes anxmStatsDuration.

callHistlocalin.name: callHistlocalin
callHistlocalin.description: The Internet (IP) address assigned to the RAC end of a point-to-point link established during this call, in dotted-decimal notation.

callHistremotein.name: callHistremotein
callHistremotein.description: The Internet (IP) address assigned to the far end of a point-to-point link established during this call, in dotted-decimal notation.

callHistlocalat.name: callHistlocalat
callHistlocalat.description: The local AppleTalk address assigned to this call.

callHistremoteat.name: callHistremoteat
callHistremoteat.description: The remote AppleTalk address assigned to this call.

callHistlocalipx.name: callHistlocalipx
callHistlocalipx.description: The local IPX address assigned to this call.

callHistremoteipx.name: callHistremoteipx
callHistremoteipx.description: The remote IPX address assigned to this call.

callHistConnectionType.name: callHistConnectionType
callHistConnectionType.description: The name of the client routine running on the port at the time of this call.

callHistOctetsRx.name: callHistOctetsRx
callHistOctetsRx.description: The number of octets received during this call.

callHistOctetsTx.name: callHistOctetsTx
callHistOctetsTx.description: The number of octets transmitted during this call.

callHistOrigin.name: callHistOrigin
callHistOrigin.description: The call origin. incoming(1) - the RAC answered an incoming call. outgoing(2) - the call was made by the RAC. This object deprecates callSetupCallType object.

callHistDisconnectReason.name: callHistDisconnectReason
callHistDisconnectReason.description: Call disconnect reasons: unknown telDisc got telephone disconnect (hangup) dialFailed wanmgrErr internal error, shouldn't happen reset WAN/channel reset admErrornext general internal mechanism to end call admModDown DSR or DCD went down pppTerm PPP protocol disconnect inactivity inactivity timer ran out hangupCmd CLI command 'hangup' lastJob CLI last-job maxLogon max logon timer ran out slaveNormal normal slave termination slaveError abnormal slave termination noCarrier modem failed to establish a connection cliInactivity cli_inactivity timer ran out portReset port was reset cliAuthFail CLI authorization failed slaveAuthFail slave port authorization failed pppPapFail PPP PAP failed pppChapFail PPP CHAP failed modemReset internal modem was reset deadModemReset internal modem was reset because it was not responding

callHistConfiguredType.name: callHistConfiguredType
callHistConfiguredType.description: The type (mode) of the port at the time of the connection. cli - allows an incoming session access to the CLI. The CLI provides access to the network and connections to other hosts via the telnet, connect, rlogin and tn3270 commands. slip - allows a port to perform as a network interface using SLIP. IP packets are encapsulated by SLIP. ppp - allows a port to perform as a network interface using PPP. Packets of several protocols are encapsulated by PPP. arap - allows a port to perform as a network interface using ARAP. slave - allows a port to accept TCP connections over the network. connect - allows a port to communicate with a LAT host via the connect command. rlogin - allows a port to communicate via the rlogin command. telnet - allows a port to communicate via the telnet command. tn3270 - allows a port to communicate via the tn3270 command.

callHistCompositeDisconnect.name: callHistCompositeDisconnect
callHistCompositeDisconnect.description: Composite call disconnect reason. Either system or modem disconnect reason (callHistDisconnectReason or callHistAsyMdmDisconnectReason). Modem reasons have 100,000 added to avoid collisions (since SNMP does not allow enum values to be negative). The modem version of 'unknown' does not occur here.

callHistOwningBundle.name: callHistOwningBundle
callHistOwningBundle.description: The identifier of the MP bundle that owns this PPP link.

callHistAsyTable.name: callHistAsyTable
callHistAsyTable.description: A table of call history asynchronous information/statistics.

callHistAsyEntry.name: callHistAsyEntry
callHistAsyEntry.description: A row in the call history async. table.

callHistAsyBeginRxSpeed.name: callHistAsyBeginRxSpeed
callHistAsyBeginRxSpeed.description: The receive connect speed when the modem connection was established.

callHistAsyEndRxSpeed.name: callHistAsyEndRxSpeed
callHistAsyEndRxSpeed.description: The ending receive connect speed of the call.

callHistAsyBeginTxSpeed.name: callHistAsyBeginTxSpeed
callHistAsyBeginTxSpeed.description: The transmit connect speed when the modem connection was established.

callHistAsyEndTxSpeed.name: callHistAsyEndTxSpeed
callHistAsyEndTxSpeed.description: The ending transmit connect speed of the call.

callHistAsyTxBaudRate.name: callHistAsyTxBaudRate
callHistAsyTxBaudRate.description: The transmit rate at which symbols that carry data are generated. Symbol rate limits and options apply to V.34. Default is r2400(1).

callHistAsyRxBaudRate.name: callHistAsyRxBaudRate

callHistAsyBeginSignalQ.name: callHistAsyBeginSignalQ
